com.poesys.db.dto

Class AbstractBatchDeleteSetter<T extends IDbDto>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractSetter<T>
      • com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractBatchDeleteSetter<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of IDbDto to delete from the owning object
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ISet, java.io.Serializable

    public abstract class AbstractBatchDeleteSetter<T extends IDbDto>
extends AbstractSetter<T>
implements ISet
    An abstract implementation of the ISet interface for a Strategy-pattern class that deletes a collection of DTOs as part of a more comprehensive transaction, taking in a connection and not closing it. The abstract methods parameterize the class with objects that the set() method uses in processing the batch delete.
    Author:
    Robert J. Muller
    See Also:

      • getBatchSize

        protected abstract int getBatchSize()
        Get the JDBC batch size, the number of rows to process in a single batch operation on the server; typically this is the number of rows expected for the list, but for very long lists it can be a partial subset such as 1,000 or 10,000. The objective is to process as many elements at a time as possible while not taking up too much memory for the transfer.
        Returns:
        the batch size
